					<p>Performed at Klub Ciglana in Belgrade, Serbia, 2015.</p>
					<p><em>Fragments</em> is an exploration into history and memory. Looking at my own Japanese family heritage as a starting point, <em>Fragments</em> seeks to explore what it means to be a part of another culture on the other side of the world. this project explores questions about the importance of understanding our pasts when it is impossible to reach an objective truth.</p>
					<p><em>Fragments</em> was initially developed as Taz’s final performance for her MA International Performance Research, and was created in combination with a 10,000 word written dissertation. For more information on the written component, please get in contact with Taz.</p>
